HEADWORD: Stroam
<hw>Stroam</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[Prov. E.
<ets>strome</ets> to walk with long strides.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
wander about idly and vacantly.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To take long strides in walking.</def> <mark>[Prov.
Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Strobila</ent>⟦br⟧
